# Contributor Onboarding

Welcome! We're excited to have you contribute to the Grant Program Management system.

## Steps to become a contributor

1. **Read the [Code of Conduct](../CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md)** – we expect all contributors to follow it.
2. **Set up the project locally** – follow the [Quick Start](../README.md#quick-start) guide.
3. **Find an issue to work on** – look for [good first issue](https://github.com/Gitdigital-products/Grant-Program-Management-repo/labels/good%20first%20issue) labels.
4. **Comment on the issue** – let others know you're working on it.
5. **Fork and clone** the repository.
6. **Create a branch** with a descriptive name (e.g., `fix-scoring-typo`).
7. **Make your changes** and commit with a clear message.
8. **Push and open a pull request** – fill out the PR template.
9. **Respond to feedback** – maintainers may request changes.
10. **Celebrate** – once merged, you're a contributor!

## What you can contribute

* **Code**: New features, bug fixes, automation improvements.
* **Documentation**: Improving guides, writing tutorials.
* **Design**: Enhancing the Pages site, creating badges/icons.
* **Community**: Helping answer questions in Discussions.

## Getting help

* Ask in the issue or PR you're working on.
* Start a [Discussion](https://github.com/Gitdigital-products/Grant-Program-Management-repo/discussions).
* Tag a maintainer with `@maintainer`.

Thank you for contributing!
```

