# Badge Authority

This directory defines the badges awarded to contributors, reviewers, and grant recipients.

## Badge Types

| Badge | Description | Awarded To | Schema |
|-------|-------------|------------|--------|
| `reviewer` | Recognizes active grant reviewers | Reviewers who complete ≥5 reviews | [reviewer-schema.json](schemas/reviewer-badge-schema.json) |
| `grantee` | Awarded to approved grant recipients | Grantees | [grantee-schema.json](schemas/grantee-badge-schema.json) |
| `contributor` | For code/documentation contributors | Contributors with merged PRs | [contributor-schema.json](schemas/contributor-badge-schema.json) |
| `sponsor` | For financial supporters | Sponsors at certain tiers | [sponsor-schema.json](schemas/sponsor-badge-schema.json) |

## Issuance Workflow

Badges are awarded automatically via GitHub Actions when certain events occur (e.g., PR merged, application approved).  
See [`.github/workflows/award-badges.yml`](../.github/workflows/award-badges.yml) for details.

Each badge is stored as a JSON file in `/badges/awarded/` with the recipient's ID and badge metadata.
```

